      World</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="https://medium.com/eidolon">Eidolon: A Modern Way to Write
      about the Ancient World</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img
      alt="https://d262ilb51hltx0.cloudfront.net/max/2000/1*bwo8jDM-SFpOebJafvl_4A.png"
      class="shrinkToFit" height="56"
      src="https://d262ilb51hltx0.cloudfront.net/max/2000/1*bwo8jDM-SFpOebJafvl_4A.png" width="200"
      /></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div class="graf--p graf--first"
      id="6a8b" name="6a8b"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><em class="markup--em
      markup--p-em">Eidolon</em> is a home for scholarly writing about Classics that isn’t
      formal scholarship. Our goal is to create a platform for essays that have a strong authorial
      voice and a unique point of view.</span></div><h4 class="graf--h4" id="ae16"
      name="ae16"><span style="font-size: x-small;">what will you see on
      Eidolon?</span></h4><div class="graf--p" id="eeb7" name="eeb7"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">We’re especially interested in submissions between 1,500 and
      2,500 words that fall into these categories:</span></div><ul
      class="postList"><li class="graf--li" id="e67b" name="e67b"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Explorations of how the ancient world relates to modern
      life</span></li><li class="graf--li" id="5e5b" name="5e5b"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">First-person, anecdotal accounts that bring pieces of classical
      art or literature to life</span></li><li class="graf--li" id="cdba"
      name="cdba"><span style="font-size: x-small;">Personal approaches to academic topics,
      especially those that embrace marginalized voices</span></li><li
      class="graf--li" id="8345" name="8345"><span style="font-size: x-small;">Risky,
      provocative arguments that push the boundaries of accepted consensus
      views</span></li><li class="graf--li" id="8ad6" name="8ad6"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Creative and funny pieces that don’t take the Classics too
      seriously</span></li></ul><div class="graf--p" id="f7cb"
      name="f7cb"><span style="font-size: x-small;">This list is by no means exhaustive. We
      expect and hope to be surprised and educated by what people
      submit.</span></div></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div
